When we have not installed Gradle on machine, we executes Tasks using Gradle wrapper. The wrapper is a script that will download and install a
specified version of Gradle.

Steps to execute Task (windows machine)
1. The important gradle files are- 
..*gradle - jar file
..*gradlew - gradle wrapper for mac/linux
..*gradlew.bat - gradle wrapper for windows
..*build.gradle - contain the tasks to perform
2. Using command prompt go to the directory containing gradle wrapper
3. Run the bat file on the prompt, if gradle is not installed, wrapper will install it
4. It will show a list of commands to run to see tasks, particular task and on.
